<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-190916" src="https://i0.wp.com/tooxclusive.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/Brymo.jpg?resize=584%2C740&#038;ssl=1" alt="" width="584" height="740" data-recalc-dims="1" /> The singer recently revealed its tracklist which consists of three parts with a total of 17 tracks. The first part which is numbered in Greek numerals consists of 6 tracks, the second part numbered in Roman numerals consists of 5 tracks and the third numbered in English numerals consists of 6 tracks. However, the singer took to his Instagram page to announce that the album would be two songs short due to technical reasons. He revealed that the songs “Iya Awele” and “Ife” did not make the cut and assured fans that the album would be released on the 1st of April as scheduled. He wrote: ” Due to technical issues there’ll be two songs less on “Yellow”… “Iya Awele” and “Ife” didn’t make the cut and I’m mad!!… but I promised the album will be in stores 1st April and the team is making sure of that… sorry about this guys.. ?????” See the post below   Due to technical issues there’ll be two songs less on “Yellow”… “Iya Awele” and “Ife” didn’t make the cut and I’m mad!!… but I promised the album will be in stores 1st April and the team is making sure of that… sorry about this guys.. ????? A post shared by  ?láwálé ?l??f???r?? (@brymolawale) on Mar 23, 2020 at 10:38am PDT //www.instagram.com/embed.js  The post Brymo Announces Removal Of Two Songs From Forthcoming Album “Yellow” appeared first on tooXclusive. Source: Too Xclusive First name * Email * Phone Number  Check your inbox or spam folder to confirm your subscription.  Sensational singer, Brymo has finally unveiled the tracklist of his forthcoming album “Yellow” which is billed to drop next month. Brymo has shared another piece of the puzzle for his “Yellow” album after releasing the artwork of the project a few days ago. With the highly anticipated album due out… March 19, 2020 In "Music/Video" Nigerian award-win